cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the use of wireless, ad-hoc, multi-hop networks for traffic coordination and regulation.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses self-organizing methods for coordinating data collection and processing, recognizing traffic phenomena, and changing their structure by coordinated behavior.
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is another possible category as the paper describes the use of distributed methods for solving traffic problems, which involves multiple agents (i.e., vehicles) interacting with each other.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses methods for pattern recognition and self-recognition of traffic jams, which are AI-related topics.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possible category as the paper describes the use of distributed methods for traffic coordination and regulation.
